Braniff Inc said a U.S. Department ofTransportation administrative law judge has recommended that acertificate be granted authorizing Braniff to operate airservice for five years on a temporary and experimental basisbetween Dallas/Fort Worth and San Antonio, Texas, and MexicoCity and Acapulco, Mexico.    The company said the recommendation must still be approvedby Transportation Secretary Elizabeth Dole and PresidentReagan. Braniff has been operating the routes under exemptionauthority granted by the Transportation Department in October. Reuter&#3;